OL,6,F"Anyone with a diarrhoeal illness
OL,7,Fshould drink plenty of water to
OL,8,Fprevent dehydration and if they have
OL,9,Fsevere symptoms like bloody diarrhoea,
OL,10,Fthey should contact NHS 111 or their
OL,11,FGP surgery.
OL,13,F"Symptoms include: watery diarrhoea,
OL,14,Fstomach pains, dehydration, weight
OL,15,Floss and fever, which can last for 2-3
OL,16,Fweeks. Anyone can get
OL,17,Fcryptosporidiosis, but it is most
OL,18,Fcommon in young children aged between
OL,19,F1 and 5 years and most healthy people
OL,20,Fwill recover fully.
